basics.label: Project Coordinator
basics.summary: To be part of a world class organization where I can utilize my experience and knowledge gained efficiently and help the organization realize its goals and objectives by focusing on optimum operational management and leadership activities.

work.name: Company
work.summary: Maintained project assets, communications and related database(s).
highlights: Review and report the project's budget and finances.
Collected information and made judgments through observation, interviews, and the review of documents.

Collaborated with economic development planners to decide on the implementation of proposed development policies, plans, and programs based on culturally institutionalized barriers and facilitating circumstances.

work.name: Company
work.summary: Established work schedules and assignments for staff, according to workload, space and equipment availability.
highlights: Conducted fiscal operations, including accounting, planning budgets, authorizing expenditures, establishing rates for services, and coordinating financial reporting.
Maintained awareness of advances in medicine, computerized diagnostic and treatment equipment, data processing technology, government regulations, health insurance changes, and financing options.

work.name: Company
work.summary: Examined teeth, gums, and related tissues, using dental instruments, x-rays, or other diagnostic equipment, to evaluate dental health, diagnose diseases or abnormalities, and plan appropriate treatments.
highlights: Completed and maintained accurate records or reports regarding the patients' histories and progress, services provided, or other required information.
Advised or instructed patients regarding preventive dental care, the causes and treatment of dental problems, or oral health care services.
